Believe it or not, there are Democrats and Republicans in this photo 👀
 
And we all agree that Members of Congress have no business trading stocks.
 
@SpeakerMcCarthy, it’s time to bring a congressional stock trading ban to the House Floor for a vote. https://t.co/RQRXSpW7rY

October is National Head Start Awareness Month.
 
@HeadStartgov provides resources to support the early childhood development of over 1 million kids in Minnesota.
 
I’ll keep working to ensure every child in Minnesota has an equal opportunity to succeed.

Mike Johnson spent his legal career fighting against same-sex marriage, adoption and marital benefits. Now he’s brought that fight to Congress.

Proud to vote against him on my 15th anniversary with my wife, Cheryl.

@RepMikeJohnson, enjoy it while it lasts - it won’t be long. https://t.co/b6UQKyiFER

Earlier this month I led the bipartisan call for a statewide USPS investigation and today they're finally listening.

@OIGUSPS will investigate the entire Minnesota-North Dakota Postal District in the coming months.

I will keep pushing for change until you get your mail on time.

For #MN02 residents currently in Lebanon:

@StateDept is telling Americans in Lebanon to submit the Crisis Intake Form linked below to help folks safely depart from the area. If you do not hear back within 24 hours, call my office at (651) 846-2120.

https://t.co/VLCT5uT4CA
